1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,142
We need to define axioms to determine

2
00:00:02,242 --> 00:00:04,445
the behaviour of this edge relation E.

3
00:00:04,533 --> 00:00:08,085
Without any axioms, every possible combination of points and all possible

4
00:00:08,185 --> 00:00:10,937
arrows drawn between them is a model of our empty theory.

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,322
An axiom can be any FOL sentence.

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,128
For example, we can consider

7
00:00:16,228 --> 00:00:18,871
this formula phi, expressing transitivity,

8
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,644
meaning that if there is some path between nodes,

9
00:00:21,744 --> 00:00:24,333
then there is a direct path between these nodes.

10
00:00:25,466 --> 00:00:30,348
Or this sentence psi expressing irreflexivity, which enforces that any

11
00:00:30,448 --> 00:00:34,405
model of it must not contain any self-referential arrows.

12
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:37,829
We can combine the sentences, and consider the collection

13
00:00:37,929 --> 00:00:40,748
of all structures which satisfy both phi and psi,

14
00:00:40,848 --> 00:00:44,621
i.e. the collection of all transitive and irreflexive structures.

15
00:00:44,666 --> 00:00:48,691
In general, given any collection of sentences Sigma, this is the

16
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:51,850
model set of Sigma, and it is the set of possible

17
00:00:51,950 --> 00:00:55,459
structures which satisfy each of the sentences in Sigma.

18
00:00:55,533 --> 00:01:00,254
Note that if Sigma contains an unsatisfiable sentence, such as x

19
00:01:00,354 --> 00:01:03,870
is not equal to x, then Mod Sigma will be empty.

20
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:06,814
And the soundness of First order logic, tells us

21
00:01:06,914 --> 00:01:09,919
that if our set of sentence Sigma is consistent...

22
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,233
then there is at least one model out

23
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:15,150
there which satisfies every formula in Sigma.

24
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,441
We see that this is based on a platonistic

25
00:01:17,541 --> 00:01:21,343
vision of mathematics, where mathematical structures are pre-existing,

26
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:26,113
and we can characterize them using first order sentences.

27
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,992
If we start to study the general structure of

28
00:01:31,092 --> 00:01:34,655
the models in Mod({phi,psi}), we might notice some things

29
00:01:34,755 --> 00:01:37,033
in common to all of these structures.

30
00:01:37,133 --> 00:01:43,198
For example we may notice that in none of them do we have aEb and bEa.

31
00:01:43,266 --> 00:01:45,550
We can easily see why, since if we did have

32
00:01:45,650 --> 00:01:48,600
such an edge in a transitive and irreflexive structure,

33
00:01:48,666 --> 00:01:53,085
then by transitivity we should have a direct path a to a.

34
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,835
But then the structure is not irreflexive, a contradiction.

35
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,592
So, we see that adding this

36
00:01:59,692 --> 00:02:02,602
sentence chi expressing assymetry, is redundant,

37
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:08,339
in the sense that Mod(phi,psi,chi) = Mod(phi,psi).

38
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:14,830
We denote this by {phi,psi} models chi.

39
00:02:14,866 --> 00:02:18,621
Recall that the deductive completeness of our calculus gives

40
00:02:18,721 --> 00:02:21,127
us a guarantee that there is a proof of

41
00:02:21,227 --> 00:02:24,275
chi from the axioms using phi,psi as assumptions.

42
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:30,082
Moving back to the world of syntax, as mentioned earlier, this

43
00:02:30,182 --> 00:02:34,619
can be seen as a computational process, where at first the

44
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:38,764
axioms are put in, and derive a new formula like chi.

45
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:43,728
Once we have derived chi, we can use

46
00:02:43,828 --> 00:02:48,757
it to prove more theorems and so on.

47
00:02:48,866 --> 00:02:53,076
In this scenario, we would say that phi and psi are axioms,

48
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:56,847
and the consequences of phi and psi are theorems.

49
00:02:56,933 --> 00:03:01,169
The theory of {phi,psi} is the set of all such theorems.

50
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:04,907
And note that as a consequence of soundness, all of these

51
00:03:05,007 --> 00:03:09,107
theorems are satisfied in every model which satisfy phi and psi.

52
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:13,062
I.e. each theorem is satisfied in every transitive and irreflexive

53
00:03:13,162 --> 00:03:15,883
structure. So we can see that the theorems of a

54
00:03:15,983 --> 00:03:18,945
given set of sentences Sigma are exactly the set of

55
00:03:19,045 --> 00:03:21,586
sentences satisfied by every model of Sigma.

